In general, for full Heusler alloys, site preferences of transition metal elements X and Y are
determined by the number of their valence electrons [75,76]: the element with more valence electrons
prefers the A and C sites yet the element with less valence electrons prefers the B site. This rule has
been widely used for explaining the atom ordering in Heusler alloy and even applied for new Heusler
design. However, there are also some studies showing the contrary results which violate this rule
[77,78]. It should be stressed that the atom ordering in Heusler alloys strongly influences their
